Before this, no disposition oi property to take effect alter one’s death, apart irorn dona- tiones mortis causa, had been valid unless the whole ol it were made uno contextu, uno eodemque ternpore: but a man ‘might now distribute his fortune in a series os fragmentary or plecemcal and unrelated disposi- tions.' lt is in this that the legal advance marked by the recognition oi codicilli oonsists, not in their ireedom from form, which was corrected by later enactments.
